  "11": {
    "John Trapp": "Therefore the heart of the king of Syria was sore troubled. ] Heb., Was tempested, or tossed with passions, as chaff is with whirlwinds, or the sea with counterblasts.\nVer.\n11. Therefore the heart of the king of Syria was sore troubled.] Heb., Was tempested, or tossed with passions, as chaff is with whirlwinds, or the sea with counterblasts.\nVer.",
    "930072315325": "Again also he sent unto him another captain of fifty with his fifty,\netc.] The king, not being at all terrified with the awful judgment upon the\nformer, sends another:\nand he answered and said unto him, O man of God, thus hath the king\nsaid, come down quickly; he flouts the prophet in the same manner as the\nformer, and in the king\u2019s name commands him to come down, and that\nimmediately; which the king added to his orders, or he himself, signifying\nhe would not be trifled with, if he did not come down directly, he would\nforce him.\nVer."
  },
